With a mission to reduce waste and protect the planet, Dyper offers diapers made from responsibly sourced bamboo, ensuring they are soft, hypoallergenic, and gentle on both babies’ skin and the environment. The company’s focus on sustainability extends to every aspect of its operations, including carbon-neutral shipping and a proprietary composting program. Dyper's groundbreaking program, REDYPER™, allows customers to compost used diapers conveniently, significantly reducing the environmental impact of traditional disposable diapers. By blending convenience with eco-conscious practices, Dyper empowers families to make greener choices without compromising on performance or comfort.

name: Daye
description: A pioneering health and wellness company dedicated to revolutionizing women’s health through innovative, sustainable, and science-backed solutions. Best known for its tampons infused with CBD to help alleviate menstrual discomfort, Daye offers products designed to empower individuals and elevate standards in gynecological care. With a strong focus on transparency and education, Daye strives to address gaps in women’s health and create a community of informed, confident users. Sustainability is at the heart of Daye's mission. The company uses organic, sustainably sourced cotton, plastic-free applicators, and biodegradable materials to minimize environmental impact. Daye also champions inclusivity and accessibility by offering subscription-based, customizable options, ensuring that its products meet diverse needs while reducing stigma around menstruation and women’s health.

name: The Positive Birth Company
description: A pioneering organization dedicated to empowering individuals and families throughout their pregnancy, birth, and postpartum journey. Founded with the mission to make high-quality, evidence-based information accessible and affordable, the company provides tools, resources, and support to help people approach childbirth with confidence and positivity. Their offerings include online hypnobirthing courses, digital support programs, and a range of practical products tailored to enhance the birth experience. Committed to inclusivity and community building, The Positive Birth Company creates a welcoming space for all parents, regardless of background or circumstance. By combining expert guidance with empathetic care, they aim to normalize and celebrate the diversity of birth experiences while promoting mental and physical well-being.

name: Real Coco
description: A health-focused beverage brand committed to providing high-quality, plant-based drinks crafted from natural coconut ingredients. With a mission to promote healthier lifestyles, Real Coco specializes in coconut water, milk, and cream, offering products free from artificial additives, preservatives, and refined sugars. The brand emphasizes simplicity and transparency, ensuring that every product delivers pure, nutrient-rich hydration and nourishment. Guided by sustainability and ethical sourcing, Real Coco works closely with farmers to harvest responsibly and support local communities. The company’s environmentally friendly practices extend to its packaging, which is designed to minimize waste and reduce its ecological footprint. Real Coco is dedicated to enhancing well-being while protecting the planet.

name: River Road Family Vineyards and Winery
description: A boutique winery located in Sonoma County, California, specializing in crafting high-quality wines that reflect the unique terroir of the Russian River Valley. Known for its artisanal approach and focus on Chardonnay and Pinot Noir, River Road combines traditional winemaking techniques with modern innovation to produce wines of exceptional character, balance, and elegance. Each bottle captures the essence of Sonoma’s cool-climate vineyards, offering a refined and approachable wine experience. With a commitment to sustainability and environmental stewardship, River Road practices eco-friendly viticulture, including water conservation, renewable energy usage, and minimal intervention in the vineyard and cellar. The winery’s dedication to quality and sustainability makes it a trusted name among wine enthusiasts seeking authentic and responsibly made wines.

name: Full Stack Supply Co
description: an innovative outdoor gear company known for designing high-performance, sustainable equipment that supports adventure seekers and outdoor enthusiasts. As the parent company of brands like Faction Skis and United Shapes, FSSC combines cutting-edge technology with eco-conscious practices to create products that enhance performance while minimizing environmental impact. With a focus on durability, quality, and responsibility, FSSC is redefining the standard for outdoor gear. Rooted in a passion for the outdoors, FSSC is committed to sustainability through the use of renewable materials, waste reduction initiatives, and partnerships with environmental organizations. The company strives to empower adventurers while preserving the natural landscapes they explore, fostering a deeper connection between people and the planet.

name: Mijenta
description: An artisanal tequila brand rooted in the rich heritage and craftsmanship of Jalisco, Mexico. Celebrated for its commitment to sustainability and quality, Mijenta produces small-batch tequilas crafted from 100% blue Weber agave, ensuring a smooth and authentic taste. The brand name, derived from the Spanish word “mi gente,” meaning “my people,” reflects its dedication to community, tradition, and the land from which it draws its inspiration. Mijenta goes beyond crafting exceptional tequila by integrating sustainability into every step of its production process. From sourcing agave grown with traditional methods to using eco-friendly packaging and supporting local artisans, Mijenta embodies environmental and social responsibility. The brand is committed to delivering a premium tequila experience while fostering a positive impact on people and the planet.

name: SunGod
description: a performance eyewear brand that specializes in creating high-quality, durable, and sustainable sunglasses and goggles. Founded on the principles of customization, innovation, and eco-consciousness, SunGod allows customers to design their own eyewear, selecting colors and features that reflect their personal style. Renowned for its lifetime guarantee, SunGod’s products are engineered with cutting-edge materials to deliver exceptional performance and withstand the demands of outdoor adventures. Sustainability is a core value at SunGod. The company uses recyclable materials, minimizes waste in its manufacturing processes, and incorporates renewable energy into its operations. Additionally, SunGod partners with environmental organizations to protect and restore ecosystems, ensuring that its commitment to the planet matches its passion for creating industry-leading eyewear.

name: Lunchskins
description: An eco-friendly lifestyle brand dedicated to reducing single-use plastic waste through its innovative reusable and compostable food storage products. Known for its stylish designs and functional solutions, Lunchskins offers a range of reusable bags, compostable sandwich bags, and other sustainable alternatives that make it easy for individuals and families to adopt greener habits. With a mission to create a healthier planet, Lunchskins combines convenience with sustainability to inspire positive change. As a Certified B Corporation, Lunchskins is committed to ethical practices, sustainability, and giving back to the community. The company actively supports environmental initiatives and has saved millions of plastic bags from ending up in landfills and oceans. Lunchskins empowers consumers to make a tangible difference in the fight against plastic pollution.

name: Radio Flyer
description: An iconic American company known for crafting high-quality, innovative wagons, tricycles, scooters, and other ride-on toys that inspire active play and create lasting memories for families. Founded in 1917, Radio Flyer has been a household name for generations, symbolizing childhood adventures and imaginative exploration. With a focus on design, durability, and safety, Radio Flyer continues to blend timeless charm with modern innovation in its products. Beyond making toys, Radio Flyer is dedicated to sustainability and social responsibility. The company integrates eco-friendly practices into its manufacturing processes, such as using renewable energy and recyclable materials, while also supporting community initiatives that promote wellness and play. Radio Flyer’s commitment to quality, innovation, and giving back ensures that it remains a trusted name in family fun.

name: Bobelo
description: A wellness-focused beverage company dedicated to creating healthy, sustainable drink solutions that prioritize both personal and planetary well-being. Specializing in effervescent hydration beverages, Bobelo’s drinks are crafted with natural ingredients, no added sugar, and functional benefits, making them a healthier alternative to traditional sodas and energy drinks. Each beverage is designed to enhance hydration while supporting a balanced, active lifestyle. Bobelo’s mission goes beyond crafting delicious drinks—it is committed to sustainability and community impact. The company uses eco-friendly, single-serve packets that reduce plastic waste and partners with organizations to support clean water initiatives. With its innovative approach to wellness and sustainability, Bobelo is redefining the way people stay hydrated and make environmentally conscious choices.

name: dryrobe
description: A premium outdoor apparel brand known for its innovative, high-performance changing robes designed to keep users warm, dry, and comfortable in any weather. Originally developed for surfers, Dryrobe has become a favorite among outdoor enthusiasts, athletes, and adventurers across various activities, including open-water swimming, triathlons, camping, and hiking. Its products are crafted with advanced materials and practical features, offering unmatched protection from the elements. With a strong commitment to sustainability, Dryrobe incorporates eco-friendly materials and practices into its production processes. The company strives to reduce its environmental impact by using recycled fabrics, minimizing waste, and supporting environmental conservation initiatives. Dryrobe’s dedication to quality, functionality, and sustainability has made it a trusted companion for outdoor adventurers worldwide.

name: Adore Me
description: An innovative lingerie and apparel brand that blends style, inclusivity, and sustainability to empower women of all shapes and sizes. Known for its commitment to diversity, the company offers an extensive range of lingerie, swimwear, activewear, and loungewear designed to celebrate individuality and confidence. With its direct-to-consumer model, Adore Me provides high-quality products at accessible prices, making fashion-forward designs available to everyone. Adore Me is deeply committed to sustainability and social responsibility. The brand incorporates eco-friendly materials, sustainable manufacturing practices, and recyclable packaging into its operations. Additionally, Adore Me’s ongoing initiatives include size inclusivity, reducing textile waste, and supporting female empowerment. By focusing on innovation and sustainability, Adore Me is reshaping the future of intimate apparel.

name: Ridgeview
description: A forward-thinking company committed to creating sustainable solutions that drive innovation while preserving our planet's resources. With a strong foundation in eco-conscious practices, Ridgeview develops products and services that empower individuals and businesses to reduce their environmental impact without compromising quality or performance. Their team of experts collaborates globally to bring innovative, green technologies to the forefront, ensuring that sustainability is at the heart of everything they do. By adhering to rigorous environmental standards and embracing a circular economy, Ridgeview demonstrates its dedication to a healthier, greener future. Their product lines reflect a commitment to energy efficiency, minimal waste, and socially responsible sourcing.

name: Muddy Puddles
description: A family-focused brand dedicated to creating high-quality, weatherproof clothing and gear for children, designed to inspire outdoor adventures in all seasons. Recognizing the importance of sustainability, the company integrates eco-friendly practices into every aspect of its operations, from responsibly sourced materials to ethical production methods. Muddy Puddles believes that nurturing a love for nature in children today is key to fostering the environmental stewards of tomorrow. Combining durability with playful designs, Muddy Puddles ensures that its products stand up to the elements while delighting children and parents alike. By committing to a balance between innovation and environmental responsibility, Muddy Puddles is redefining outdoor apparel for young explorers.

name: The Organic Company
description: A visionary leader in sustainable living, offering a range of thoughtfully designed organic textiles that blend functionality, elegance, and environmental consciousness. Founded on the principles of sustainability and responsible production, the company is dedicated to creating products that positively impact the planet while enhancing everyday life. Each item in their collection is crafted with certified organic cotton, ensuring the highest quality and a minimal ecological footprint. The Organic Company’s mission extends beyond its products, advocating for a lifestyle that prioritizes mindful consumption and respect for natural resources. Their commitment to transparency, fair trade, and environmental stewardship has established them as a trusted brand for conscious consumers worldwide.

name: Baileys
description: A globally recognized brand renowned for its luxurious cream liqueurs that combine rich Irish dairy cream with fine spirits and flavors. Established in Ireland, Baileys embodies a unique blend of heritage, craftsmanship, and indulgence, creating a product beloved by consumers around the world. Known for its iconic Original Irish Cream, Baileys has expanded its offerings to include innovative flavors and non-dairy options, appealing to a diverse audience while maintaining its reputation for quality and taste. Rooted in sustainability, Baileys has embraced eco-conscious practices across its supply chain. From sourcing local ingredients to adopting sustainable packaging solutions, the company is committed to minimizing its environmental impact while delivering a premium experience to its customers.

name: Isle of Wight Distillery
description: A celebrated craft distillery located on the picturesque Isle of Wight, producing award-winning spirits inspired by the natural beauty and heritage of the island. Known for its commitment to quality and sustainability, the distillery creates small-batch gins, vodkas, and rums, including its flagship Mermaid Gin, which reflects its coastal origins with a fresh, oceanic profile. With a focus on reducing environmental impact, the Isle of Wight Distillery adopts eco-friendly practices in its production and packaging, using recyclable materials and responsibly sourced ingredients. Their dedication to local craftsmanship and sustainability has earned them a loyal following and a reputation as a responsible, community-centered brand.

name: Icebug
description: A Swedish footwear company dedicated to creating innovative and sustainable outdoor shoes that excel in challenging conditions. Known for their advanced traction technology, Icebug shoes are designed to provide safety and confidence on slippery surfaces, making them ideal for outdoor enthusiasts and urban explorers alike. The company's commitment to sustainability is evident in its use of recycled and bio-based materials, as well as its ambitious goal to minimize its environmental footprint. As one of the first climate-positive outdoor footwear brands, Icebug actively works to offset more carbon than it emits. Through partnerships with environmental organizations and continuous innovation in sustainable materials, the company leads by example, showcasing how businesses can succeed while prioritizing ecological responsibility.

name: Optimist Drinks
description: A Los Angeles-based brand that crafts non-alcoholic spirits designed to enhance social experiences while promoting mental and physical well-being. With a mission to foster inclusivity and encourage mindful drinking, Optimist Drinks offers a range of botanical blends inspired by the vibrant landscapes of California. Their products are perfect for creating sophisticated, alcohol-free cocktails that cater to a growing audience seeking healthier lifestyle choices. Sustainability and giving back are at the core of Optimist Drinks' operations. The company emphasizes using responsibly sourced ingredients and eco-friendly packaging while donating a portion of its proceeds to mental health initiatives. Optimist Drinks embodies a positive approach to living well, inspiring its customers to embrace mindful consumption.

name: The Duppy Share
description: A London-based rum brand that captures the vibrant spirit of the Caribbean with its range of premium blends. The name is inspired by Caribbean folklore, where the "duppy" is a mischievous spirit that takes the best share of the rum. Known for its award-winning golden and spiced rums, The Duppy Share combines the finest aged rums from Barbados and Jamaica to create a bold, authentic, and modern expression of Caribbean culture. The company is deeply committed to sustainability and community empowerment. Through eco-friendly packaging, carbon offsetting initiatives, and partnerships with Caribbean communities, The Duppy Share supports cultural and environmental sustainability while bringing a taste of the tropics to a global audience.

name: Wayb
description: A mission-driven brand that designs eco-friendly and innovative travel gear for families on the go. Known for its award-winning Pico Travel Car Seat, WAYB creates products that prioritize safety, convenience, and sustainability. The company’s commitment to the environment is evident in its use of responsibly sourced materials, such as recycled aluminum and polyester, to produce lightweight and durable products that meet the highest safety standards. Founded with the goal of making travel easier and greener for modern families, WAYB ensures its designs align with eco-conscious values without compromising on functionality or style. By combining thoughtful design with environmental responsibility, WAYB empowers families to explore the world sustainably.

name: Vital Proteins
description: A leading health and wellness brand specializing in premium collagen-based supplements designed to support overall health and well-being. Founded in 2013, the company is dedicated to helping people live their healthiest lives by providing products that promote healthy skin, hair, nails, joints, and gut health. Vital Proteins’ flagship product, Collagen Peptides, has become a staple for individuals looking to enhance their daily wellness routine. Sustainability is a core value at Vital Proteins, with efforts focused on responsibly sourcing ingredients and minimizing environmental impact. By prioritizing transparency and quality, the company ensures its products are non-GMO, free from artificial flavors, and made with clean, high-quality ingredients.

name: Beckett Simonon
description: A direct-to-consumer footwear and accessories brand that blends traditional craftsmanship with sustainable practices. Based in Bogotá, Colombia, the company offers high-quality, made-to-order leather goods, including shoes, belts, and bags, crafted by skilled artisans. By adopting a pre-order model, Beckett Simonon minimizes waste and ensures ethical production while providing customers with luxury products at accessible prices. The brand is deeply committed to sustainability and fair labor practices, using responsibly sourced materials like full-grain leather from gold-rated tanneries. By prioritizing transparency and slow fashion principles, Beckett Simonon delivers timeless, durable goods that align with modern eco-conscious and ethical values.

name: Risedesk
description: A leading innovator in ergonomic office furniture, designed to enhance productivity and support health in the workplace. Based in Canada, the company specializes in height-adjustable standing desks, ergonomic chairs, and office accessories that prioritize comfort, functionality, and style. RiseDesk is committed to creating a seamless work experience by offering customizable solutions that cater to individual needs and preferences. Sustainability is a core pillar of RiseDesk’s operations, reflected in its use of eco-friendly materials and processes. The company emphasizes durability and responsible sourcing to minimize its environmental footprint while delivering high-quality, long-lasting products. RiseDesk empowers customers to build healthier, more sustainable workspaces.

name: Gran Luchito
description: An authentic Mexican food brand dedicated to bringing bold, traditional flavors to kitchens around the world. Founded in the UK, the company offers a wide range of handcrafted products, including salsas, cooking sauces, tortillas, and snacks. Each product is made with carefully selected, high-quality ingredients sourced directly from Mexico, ensuring an authentic and vibrant taste experience. The brand is committed to sustainability and ethical sourcing, working closely with small-scale farmers in Mexico to support local communities and preserve traditional agricultural practices. Gran Luchito’s mission is to celebrate the richness of Mexican cuisine while promoting eco-conscious and socially responsible practices.

name: Buff
description: A globally recognized outdoor brand specializing in multifunctional headwear and accessories designed for adventure, sports, and everyday use. Founded in Spain, the company revolutionized the outdoor gear market with its original tubular headwear, which combines functionality, comfort, and style. BUFF® products are crafted to protect against the elements, offering versatile solutions for sun, wind, and cold weather, making them a favorite among outdoor enthusiasts worldwide. BUFF® is deeply committed to sustainability, utilizing recycled and eco-friendly materials such as recycled polyester from plastic bottles. The company actively reduces its environmental impact through sustainable production processes and by supporting initiatives that protect the planet’s natural ecosystems.

name: Shine Pet Food Co.
description: Formerly known as Marty's Meals, is a Santa Fe-based company specializing in handcrafted, organic-certified pet foods for cats and dogs. Founded in 2010 by Sandra Bosben, the company emphasizes sustainability, transparency, and the use of high-quality, human-grade ingredients sourced from local ranches and farms. Their product line includes over 40 certified organic items, all made by hand and sustainably sourced, with a commitment to environmental impact, social impact, nutrition, and animal welfare.

name: Partake Foods
description: A Black-owned, women-led company specializing in allergy-friendly snacks that are certified gluten-free, non-GMO, vegan, and free from the top nine allergens, including wheat, tree nuts, peanuts, milk, eggs, soy, fish, sesame, and shellfish. Founded in 2016 by Denise Woodard after her daughter was diagnosed with multiple food allergies, the company aims to provide inclusive, delicious, and safe food options for individuals with and without dietary restrictions.

name: Project Hive Pet Company
description: A forward-thinking enterprise dedicated to crafting sustainable and innovative pet products that cater to the needs of pets and the planet. With a mission to promote environmental consciousness in pet ownership, the company offers a diverse range of toys, treats, and accessories designed to engage pets while leaving a minimal environmental footprint. Through rigorous sustainability initiatives, Project Hive Pet Company has become a trusted name for eco-conscious pet owners who value quality, ethics, and sustainability. At the heart of their operations is a commitment to sustainability and ethical practices, ensuring that every product is responsibly sourced and produced. The company integrates innovative materials such as recycled plastics and biodegradable components into its designs, prioritizing the well-being of pets and the environment. Project Hive Pet Company continually invests in eco-friendly practices, contributing to a healthier planet and fostering an ever-growing community of environmentally responsible pet owners.

name: Marine Layer
description: A lifestyle apparel brand renowned for its focus on creating ultra-soft, sustainable clothing that combines comfort and style. Founded with the mission to offer high-quality, eco-conscious casual wear, the company has carved out a niche for producing timeless pieces designed to become wardrobe staples. Marine Layer emphasizes sustainability at every step, from sourcing renewable materials to implementing innovative recycling programs, making it a favorite among environmentally aware consumers. At its core, Marine Layer is dedicated to reducing environmental impact while maintaining impeccable quality. Through initiatives like their Re-Spun recycling program, the company collects old T-shirts and gives them new life, turning waste into a resource. Marine Layer blends laid-back aesthetics with a commitment to sustainability, ensuring that their clothing is as good for the planet as it is for their customers.

name: Orgain
description: a leading health and wellness company specializing in clean, organic nutritional products designed to support active and healthy lifestyles. Founded by a cancer survivor and medical doctor, Orgain's mission is to provide high-quality, plant-based, and organic nutrition without compromising on taste or efficacy. Their product line includes protein powders, meal replacements, shakes, and bars crafted with thoughtfully selected ingredients, free from artificial additives, GMOs, and preservatives. At its core, Orgain emphasizes the connection between wholesome nutrition and well-being, striving to make clean eating accessible to everyone. The company combines scientific expertise with sustainable practices, ensuring that their products not only nourish the body but also respect the planet. By catering to a wide range of dietary needs, including vegan, gluten-free, and keto, Orgain has become a trusted name in the realm of health-conscious nutrition.

name: TWOTHIRDS
description: An eco-conscious fashion brand deeply rooted in sustainability and ocean preservation. Inspired by the fact that two-thirds of our planet is covered by water, the brand’s mission is to create high-quality, timeless clothing that minimizes environmental impact. TwoThirds focuses on sustainable materials, ethical production practices, and transparency to ensure their apparel aligns with their vision of protecting the oceans. Dedicated to reducing overproduction and waste, TwoThirds operates on a pre-order model, crafting products only when they are ordered. This unique approach eliminates excess inventory and ensures every piece is made with care and precision. By using organic and recycled fabrics, TwoThirds helps its customers make environmentally friendly choices without sacrificing style or quality.

name: Pure Table Top
description: A leading innovator in stylish and sustainable homeware, specializing in thoughtfully designed tableware, kitchen accessories, and home décor. With a mission to blend modern aesthetics with sustainability, Pure Table Top offers high-quality products that bring elegance and eco-consciousness into homes. Their collections are carefully crafted using sustainable materials like bamboo, recycled glass, and organic fabrics, aligning with their commitment to protecting the planet. The company stands out for its dedication to transparency and responsible practices, working with ethical suppliers and minimizing waste in its production processes. Pure Table Top aims to inspire customers to make mindful choices by offering timeless, durable products that enrich daily living while reducing environmental impact.

name: Topiku
description: An eco-conscious fashion brand specializing in sustainable headwear crafted from upcycled and recycled materials. Rooted in its commitment to environmental responsibility, the company transforms waste such as fabric scraps, plastic bottles, and other discarded materials into stylish and durable hats. Topiku’s mission extends beyond sustainable production; it also aims to empower local communities by partnering with skilled artisans in Indonesia, ensuring fair wages and ethical working conditions. Every Topiku product reflects a dedication to quality, creativity, and sustainability. By focusing on upcycling and minimizing environmental impact, the company provides an eco-friendly alternative to traditional fashion, encouraging consumers to make mindful choices. Topiku is more than a brand—it's a movement to reimagine waste as a valuable resource and to promote sustainable fashion practices globally.

name: ooni
description: A trailblazing company revolutionizing the art of outdoor cooking with its high-performance, portable pizza ovens. Founded on a passion for delicious, wood-fired pizza, Ooni empowers pizza enthusiasts to create restaurant-quality pies at home in as little as 60 seconds. Known for their innovative designs, Ooni ovens are versatile, easy to use, and fueled by sustainable energy sources like wood pellets, gas, and charcoal. Beyond their product excellence, Ooni is deeply committed to sustainability and social responsibility. The company actively participates in environmental initiatives, such as planting trees for every oven sold, and advocates for reducing carbon footprints through thoughtful design and operations. By blending functionality, style, and eco-consciousness, Ooni has become a global leader in the outdoor cooking space.

name: Aveda
description: A global leader in the beauty industry, renowned for its commitment to sustainability, wellness, and naturally derived products. Established with the philosophy of combining beauty with environmental responsibility, Aveda creates high-performance hair, skin, and body care products using botanically based ingredients. The brand is dedicated to minimizing its ecological footprint while delivering luxurious, salon-quality results. Aveda’s holistic approach extends beyond its products to encompass sustainable manufacturing, renewable energy use, and philanthropic initiatives that support global environmental causes. As a pioneer in eco-conscious beauty, Aveda sets the standard for blending natural elements with cutting-edge science to provide products that are both effective and environmentally responsible.

name: Ancient Nutrition
description: A wellness brand dedicated to delivering high-quality nutritional products inspired by ancient traditions and backed by modern science. Specializing in supplements, collagen, and protein powders, the company integrates whole-food ingredients and traditional remedies to support optimal health and well-being. Ancient Nutrition’s mission is to empower individuals to live healthier, more vibrant lives by reconnecting them with the benefits of natural, nutrient-dense products. At the heart of its philosophy is a commitment to sustainability and regenerative farming practices. Ancient Nutrition sources ingredients responsibly and incorporates environmentally friendly methods to reduce its ecological footprint. The brand is a trusted leader in health and wellness, offering a range of products that cater to diverse dietary needs and health goals.

name: Project Reef
description: A forward-thinking skincare brand dedicated to providing reef-safe, eco-friendly products that protect both your skin and the planet. Specializing in sunscreen and skincare products, the company emphasizes using clean, natural ingredients that are free from harmful chemicals like oxybenzone and octinoxate, which can damage coral reefs. Project Reef is committed to creating high-performance, non-toxic products that cater to environmentally conscious consumers without compromising on quality. Beyond skincare, Project Reef actively contributes to marine conservation efforts, partnering with organizations to restore coral reefs and promote ocean health. By blending effective skincare solutions with a strong environmental mission, Project Reef empowers individuals to make choices that are better for their skin and the oceans.

name: Cariloha
description: A luxury lifestyle brand that blends comfort and sustainability through its unique bamboo-based products. From bedding and bath essentials to clothing and accessories, Cariloha transforms bamboo into luxuriously soft and eco-friendly fabrics that are both durable and sustainable. The company is dedicated to promoting sustainable living, leveraging bamboo’s naturally renewable qualities to craft products that benefit consumers and the planet alike. Cariloha’s commitment to sustainability extends beyond its materials. The brand employs eco-conscious practices across its manufacturing and operations, ensuring minimal environmental impact. With a focus on providing high-quality, stylish, and sustainable products, Cariloha has become a trusted choice for individuals seeking to enhance their comfort while supporting environmentally responsible practices.

name: Bambino Mio
description: A globally recognized brand specializing in reusable cloth diapers and eco-friendly baby products. Founded on the principles of sustainability and quality, Bambino Mio provides parents with an environmentally friendly alternative to disposable diapers, helping reduce waste while offering comfort and functionality. Their products are designed with both babies and the planet in mind, featuring soft, safe materials and stylish designs that cater to modern families. Bambino Mio is committed to making sustainable parenting accessible by offering a wide range of reusable nappies, swimwear, and accessories. The company actively promotes eco-conscious practices and educates parents about the environmental and financial benefits of reusable diapering. With a mission to protect the planet for future generations, Bambino Mio combines innovative design with a passion for sustainability.

name: Ethanology Distillation
description: A boutique craft distillery celebrated for its artisanal approach to creating high-quality, small-batch spirits. Located in the heart of Michigan, the distillery is dedicated to using locally sourced, organic ingredients and innovative techniques to produce distinctive spirits that honor the region's rich agricultural heritage. Ethanology takes pride in its commitment to craftsmanship, sustainability, and community, making it a standout in the craft distilling industry. At Ethanology, every bottle tells a story of dedication to quality and the environment. The distillery emphasizes eco-conscious practices, from sourcing grains and botanicals from nearby farms to using energy-efficient distillation methods. By combining artistry and sustainability, Ethanology delivers a premium drinking experience that reflects its values and passion for innovation.

name: Plank Hardware
description: A design-forward brand specializing in high-quality, stylish hardware for homes and interiors. Focused on blending functionality with aesthetics, the company offers a wide range of cabinet handles, drawer pulls, hooks, and other hardware pieces designed to elevate any space. Plank Hardware’s commitment to thoughtful design and craftsmanship ensures that its products are not only durable but also timelessly elegant. The brand places a strong emphasis on sustainability, employing environmentally friendly materials and practices throughout its operations. By focusing on both innovative design and eco-conscious production, Plank Hardware has become a trusted choice for homeowners, interior designers, and renovators who value style, quality, and environmental responsibility.

name: The Boatyard Distillery
description: A craft distillery known for producing premium spirits with a deep connection to its coastal heritage. Located on the shores of Fermanagh in Northern Ireland, the distillery combines traditional techniques with modern innovation to create award-winning gin, whiskey, and other spirits. Each product is carefully crafted using locally sourced botanicals and pure water from nearby lakes, ensuring a distinctive flavor that reflects its origin. Sustainability and craftsmanship are at the heart of The Boatyard Distillery’s operations. The distillery is committed to minimizing its environmental footprint through sustainable practices, such as sourcing ingredients locally and utilizing eco-friendly packaging. By combining its passion for exceptional spirits with a respect for the environment, The Boatyard Distillery has established itself as a leading name in artisanal distilling.

name: goodbuy
description: An innovative online platform that connects conscious consumers with small, independent businesses offering sustainable and ethically made products. By curating a diverse marketplace of goods ranging from home essentials to fashion, GoodBuy empowers shoppers to make choices that support local economies and environmentally friendly practices. The platform’s mission is to create a more equitable and sustainable future by making it easy for consumers to shop responsibly. GoodBuy takes pride in its commitment to transparency and community building. Each business featured on the platform is carefully vetted to ensure alignment with ethical standards, such as fair labor practices, sustainable sourcing, and eco-friendly packaging. Through education and advocacy, GoodBuy inspires a shift towards mindful consumption, fostering a marketplace that prioritizes people and the planet over profit.

name: Pyzel Surfboards
description: A world-renowned surfboard brand celebrated for its high-performance designs and commitment to quality craftsmanship. Founded by master shaper Jon Pyzel in Hawaii, the brand has become a favorite among professional surfers and enthusiasts alike, offering a wide range of boards tailored to different surf styles and conditions. From shortboards to big wave guns, Pyzel Surfboards combines innovative design with decades of expertise to deliver boards that enhance performance and provide unparalleled wave-riding experiences. Beyond performance, Pyzel Surfboards embraces sustainability and eco-conscious practices, striving to minimize its environmental impact. The company incorporates sustainable materials, such as eco-friendly resins and recycled foam blanks, into its manufacturing process and continually explores new methods to reduce waste. By balancing performance and sustainability, Pyzel Surfboards has established itself as a leader in the surfing community.

name: 818 Tequila
description: A premium tequila brand known for its commitment to craftsmanship, sustainability, and social responsibility. Crafted in Jalisco, Mexico, 818 Tequila offers a range of smooth, high-quality tequilas made from 100% Blue Weber agave. The brand emphasizes traditional production methods, including slow cooking and fermentation, to create a refined taste profile that appeals to tequila enthusiasts worldwide. Beyond its exceptional spirits, 818 Tequila is deeply committed to sustainable and ethical practices. The company partners with local farmers and distillers, ensuring fair wages and supporting the local community. Additionally, 818 implements eco-conscious measures, such as recycling agave waste and using renewable energy in its production process, reflecting its dedication to environmental stewardship.

name: Back Market
description: A leading online marketplace specializing in refurbished electronics, offering consumers a sustainable and cost-effective alternative to purchasing new devices. Founded with the mission to reduce e-waste and promote circular economy practices, Back Market connects customers with certified refurbishers who restore devices to like-new condition. The platform features a wide range of products, including smartphones, laptops, tablets, and home appliances, all backed by warranties and stringent quality standards. As a pioneer in sustainable technology, Back Market is committed to combating the environmental impact of electronic waste by extending the lifecycle of devices. The company actively promotes responsible consumption and transparency, empowering customers to make eco-friendly choices without compromising quality or performance. Back Market is more than just a marketplace—it's a movement toward a more sustainable tech industry.

name: Marphyl
description: A sustainable and eco-conscious brand specializing in all-natural, multi-purpose marine phytoplankton products. Harnessing the power of the ocean, Marphyl offers a range of organic soil enhancers, pet supplements, and health products that are rich in nutrients and derived from 100% pure marine phytoplankton. The company’s mission is to promote environmental sustainability and healthy living by utilizing one of nature’s most powerful and renewable resources. Marphyl is committed to maintaining the delicate balance of marine ecosystems. By sustainably harvesting marine phytoplankton and employing environmentally friendly production practices, the company ensures that its products are not only effective but also contribute to the health of the planet. Marphyl empowers individuals to make greener choices, whether nurturing their plants, pets, or personal well-being.

name: FatFace
description: A British lifestyle clothing and accessories brand known for its relaxed, comfortable, and versatile designs. Inspired by a love of the outdoors and a spirit of adventure, FatFace creates clothing that seamlessly blends practicality and style, catering to men, women, and children. The brand focuses on providing high-quality, timeless pieces that support active and casual lifestyles, from coastal walks to city outings. FatFace is also committed to sustainability, actively integrating eco-conscious materials and ethical practices into its operations. The company works toward reducing its environmental impact by using sustainable fabrics, adopting circular fashion initiatives, and partnering with ethical suppliers. With a mission to deliver stylish yet responsible products, FatFace is a brand that values both people and the planet.

name: Dr. Squatch
description: A natural personal care brand dedicated to crafting high-quality grooming products for men. Known for its signature natural soaps, shampoos, deodorants, and other hygiene essentials, Dr. Squatch uses only sustainably sourced ingredients to create products that are gentle on the skin and free from harsh chemicals. The brand’s mission is to elevate men’s grooming routines with products that are effective, eco-friendly, and distinctly masculine. Rooted in transparency and environmental responsibility, Dr. Squatch takes pride in delivering products that prioritize health and sustainability. With fun, relatable branding and a commitment to clean ingredients, the company has become a trusted name in natural men’s grooming. Dr. Squatch empowers men to embrace self-care while making environmentally responsible choices.

name: The Honest Bison
description: A premium meat company dedicated to providing 100% grass-fed, ethically raised bison, elk, and beef products. Founded on the principles of honesty and transparency, the company partners with small, sustainable ranchers to ensure its animals are raised in open pastures without hormones, antibiotics, or feedlots. With a mission to promote regenerative agriculture and nutrient-dense diets, The Honest Bison offers high-quality meats that are as good for the planet as they are for your health. The company’s commitment to sustainability extends beyond its farming practices. By supporting regenerative farming, The Honest Bison helps restore soil health, reduce carbon emissions, and maintain ecological balance. The brand empowers consumers to make responsible food choices by offering clean, responsibly sourced meats with full traceability.

name: Kase Custom
description: a design-focused brand specializing in creating bespoke, handcrafted furniture tailored to individual tastes and needs. Known for its exceptional craftsmanship and attention to detail, the company offers custom-made furniture pieces ranging from tables and chairs to shelving and cabinetry. Kase Custom Furniture combines timeless aesthetics with functionality, making each piece a unique addition to any home or workspace. Sustainability lies at the heart of Kase Custom Furniture's ethos. The company prioritizes eco-friendly practices by sourcing responsibly harvested wood, incorporating reclaimed materials, and utilizing low-VOC finishes. By blending innovative design with sustainable production, Kase Custom Furniture delivers products that are built to last while contributing to a healthier planet.

name: Every Man Jack
description: A leading personal care brand dedicated to crafting high-quality grooming products for men using naturally derived and eco-friendly ingredients. With a mission to provide clean, effective, and affordable solutions, the brand offers a comprehensive range of products, including shampoos, body washes, deodorants, skincare, and shaving essentials. Every Man Jack stands out for its commitment to creating products that cater to the needs of men while prioritizing the health of the planet. At the core of its philosophy is a focus on sustainability and transparency. Every Man Jack utilizes responsibly sourced materials, recyclable packaging, and manufacturing practices that minimize environmental impact. By blending performance with purpose, the brand has become a trusted name for men seeking natural, ethical grooming products.

name: Tru Earth
description: An innovative eco-friendly brand specializing in zero-waste household cleaning products. Best known for its laundry detergent strips, Tru Earth offers a revolutionary approach to cleaning with compact, lightweight, and biodegradable solutions that significantly reduce plastic waste. Committed to sustainability and simplicity, Tru Earth empowers consumers to make environmentally responsible choices without compromising on cleaning performance. With a mission to combat the global plastic crisis, Tru Earth incorporates sustainable practices in every aspect of its operations. The brand focuses on reducing carbon emissions, eliminating single-use plastics, and promoting education on the environmental benefits of zero-waste living. Tru Earth’s products are designed to be effective, affordable, and accessible, inspiring a movement toward a cleaner planet.

name: OLPRO
description: A leading UK-based brand specializing in high-quality outdoor leisure products, including tents, campervan awnings, and camping accessories. Designed for outdoor enthusiasts, OLPRO’s products combine innovative features, stylish designs, and durability to enhance camping and outdoor experiences. With a strong focus on customer satisfaction, OLPRO offers gear that is easy to use, functional, and perfect for families, adventurers, and festival-goers alike. OLPRO is committed to sustainability and environmental responsibility. The brand incorporates eco-friendly materials and manufacturing practices while actively participating in tree-planting initiatives to offset its carbon footprint. By blending innovation with eco-consciousness, OLPRO ensures that adventurers can enjoy the great outdoors responsibly.

name: Goodnature
description: A pioneering brand specializing in humane, automatic pest control solutions designed to protect homes, farms, and natural ecosystems. Known for its innovative self-resetting traps, Goodnature offers an eco-friendly and non-toxic approach to pest control, effectively targeting species such as rats and mice without the use of harmful chemicals. Built for durability and ease of use, Goodnature traps are powered by CO₂ canisters, ensuring consistent, humane operation. Committed to sustainability, Goodnature creates products that align with its vision of a balanced coexistence between humans and wildlife. By reducing the reliance on poisons and single-use traps, the company helps minimize harm to non-target species and the environment. Trusted globally, Goodnature is dedicated to making pest control safe, effective, and sustainable.

name: ROKA London
description: A contemporary lifestyle brand celebrated for its stylish, functional, and sustainable backpacks, bags, and accessories. Known for blending innovative design with practicality, Roka London’s products are crafted to suit modern, on-the-go lifestyles. From commuters and travelers to students and parents, Roka’s collections cater to individuals seeking versatile and durable bags that make a statement. At the core of Roka London’s ethos is a commitment to sustainability and ethical practices. The brand incorporates recycled materials, such as recycled PET (rPET) bottles, into its manufacturing process, creating eco-conscious products that minimize environmental impact. With a focus on quality, design, and sustainability, Roka London empowers customers to choose products that are as kind to the planet as they are to their personal style.

name: Cleanery
description: A sustainable cleaning products brand that prioritizes eco-friendly innovation and effectiveness. With a mission to transform the way people clean, Cleanery offers a range of non-toxic, biodegradable, and refillable cleaning solutions for homes and businesses. Their products are designed to minimize environmental impact while delivering exceptional cleaning performance, making it easier for consumers to adopt greener practices in their everyday lives. Committed to sustainability, Cleanery emphasizes the use of plant-based ingredients, recyclable packaging, and a closed-loop refill system to reduce plastic waste. By focusing on transparency, safety, and environmental responsibility, Cleanery empowers customers to maintain a clean home while contributing to a cleaner planet.

name: GOT BAG
description: A pioneering eco-conscious brand known for creating the world’s first backpacks made from recycled ocean plastic. Founded with a mission to fight plastic pollution, the company transforms collected marine debris into durable, stylish, and functional bags and accessories. Got Bag’s innovative approach combines sustainability with high-quality craftsmanship, appealing to environmentally conscious consumers seeking products that make a positive impact. With sustainability at its core, Got Bag partners with coastal communities and cleanup initiatives to retrieve plastic waste from the oceans. The company promotes a circular economy by giving discarded materials a second life, helping to reduce environmental harm while raising awareness about the global plastic crisis. Got Bag empowers individuals to join the movement toward cleaner oceans and more sustainable living.

name: Ekster
description: A leading innovator in smart wallets and everyday carry accessories, blending sleek design with advanced technology. Known for its minimalist, RFID-blocking wallets with built-in tracking capabilities, Ekster has revolutionized the way people organize and protect their essentials. The brand combines premium materials such as leather and aluminum with state-of-the-art features, creating functional, stylish solutions for modern lifestyles. Sustainability is at the heart of Ekster’s operations. The company uses eco-friendly materials, including recycled aluminum and sustainably sourced leather, while incorporating solar-powered tracking technology to reduce reliance on disposable batteries. With a commitment to quality, innovation, and environmental responsibility, Ekster offers products that align with the values of convenience, security, and sustainability.

name: Fraser tea
description: A family-owned company dedicated to crafting premium, organic teas that promote wellness and sustainability. With a deep passion for tea culture, Fraser Tea offers an extensive collection of handcrafted blends, ranging from classic black and green teas to innovative herbal infusions. Each tea is thoughtfully curated using the finest organic ingredients, ensuring exceptional taste and quality. At the core of Fraser Tea’s mission is a commitment to environmental responsibility and ethical sourcing. The company partners with certified organic and fair-trade farms to support sustainable agriculture while maintaining the highest standards of purity. By combining artisanal craftsmanship with eco-conscious practices, Fraser Tea provides a guilt-free indulgence for tea lovers around the globe.

name: BeatBox
description: A vibrant and innovative beverage brand that has redefined party drinks with its range of delicious, portable, and eco-conscious alcohol products. Known for its unique, ready-to-drink wine-based cocktails, BeatBox offers bold flavors like Blue Razzberry and Pink Lemonade in convenient, eco-friendly packaging. The brand’s mission is to deliver fun, flavorful beverages that elevate social gatherings while prioritizing sustainability. Committed to reducing its environmental impact, BeatBox uses recyclable, carbon-neutral packaging and actively supports environmental and social initiatives. With its fresh approach to beverages and a dedication to sustainability, BeatBox has become a go-to choice for consumers seeking a mix of fun, convenience, and environmental responsibility.

name: Huel
description: A globally recognized brand that offers nutritionally complete, plant-based meals designed to provide convenience, sustainability, and balanced nutrition. With a mission to make healthy eating effortless, Huel produces ready-to-drink meals, powders, and bars that contain all 26 essential vitamins and minerals, as well as a perfect blend of protein, carbs, fats, and fiber. Its products are ideal for busy individuals seeking a convenient yet nutritious alternative to traditional meals. Huel stands out not only for its commitment to health but also for its dedication to sustainability. The company prioritizes the use of vegan ingredients, minimal packaging, and carbon-conscious production processes to reduce its environmental footprint. By combining science-backed nutrition with eco-conscious practices, Huel empowers consumers to live healthier, more sustainable lifestyles.

name: OnceUpon
description: A modern storytelling platform dedicated to helping people preserve and share their cherished memories through beautifully crafted photo books. With an easy-to-use app, OnceUpon empowers users to turn their photos and stories into elegant, high-quality albums in just a few clicks. The brand is rooted in the belief that every story deserves to be told and preserved, offering a seamless way to celebrate life’s moments. OnceUpon is committed to sustainability and quality. All photo books are made using responsibly sourced materials and eco-friendly printing processes, ensuring a minimal environmental footprint. With its combination of simplicity, personalization, and environmental consciousness, OnceUpon has become a trusted choice for creating timeless keepsakes.

name: Mary Ruth's
description: A trusted wellness brand specializing in clean, high-quality vitamins, supplements, and health products for the whole family. Founded with a mission to support healthier lifestyles, MaryRuth’s offers an extensive range of products, including liquid vitamins, gummies, probiotics, and herbal blends. The brand emphasizes using non-GMO, plant-based ingredients that are free from common allergens, making its products accessible to a wide range of dietary needs and preferences. MaryRuth’s is deeply committed to transparency, sustainability, and customer well-being. By prioritizing eco-friendly practices and rigorous testing, the company ensures that every product is safe, effective, and environmentally responsible. With a focus on simplicity, purity, and care, MaryRuth’s has become a leading name in the health and wellness industry.

name: Definite Articles
description: A sustainable clothing brand redefining the basics with eco-friendly, performance-driven underwear and essentials. Designed for comfort, durability, and minimal environmental impact, the brand uses innovative materials like recycled and biodegradable fabrics to craft products that look good, feel good, and are kind to the planet. Definite Articles caters to individuals who value high-quality essentials that align with their commitment to sustainability. At the heart of Definite Articles is a dedication to transparency, sustainability, and ethical production. By using cutting-edge technology and partnering with responsible manufacturers, the brand ensures its products are crafted with precision and care. Definite Articles is paving the way for a more conscious approach to everyday clothing, combining function, style, and environmental stewardship.

name: Opella
description: a global pharmaceutical company committed to improving health outcomes through innovative, high-quality medications and healthcare solutions. Focused on addressing a wide range of therapeutic needs, Opella Pharmaceuticals develops, manufactures, and distributes medicines that enhance patient care and well-being. The company’s mission is to make healthcare accessible and effective, driving advancements in medicine through research and development. Rooted in sustainability and corporate responsibility, Opella Pharmaceuticals integrates environmentally friendly practices into its operations while adhering to the highest ethical standards. By prioritizing patient needs, safety, and sustainability, Opella Pharmaceuticals strives to contribute to a healthier and more equitable world.

name: OLIPOP
description: A modern beverage brand redefining soda by offering a delicious, gut-friendly alternative that combines nostalgia with health benefits. Crafted with a blend of prebiotics, plant fiber, and botanicals, Olipop sodas support digestive health while delivering the classic taste of traditional sodas without excessive sugar or artificial ingredients. With flavors like Vintage Cola, Strawberry Vanilla, and Orange Cream, Olipop bridges the gap between indulgence and wellness. At its core, Olipop is committed to promoting healthier lifestyles and sustainability. The company uses eco-friendly practices, including recyclable packaging and responsibly sourced ingredients, to minimize its environmental impact. By balancing taste, nutrition, and sustainability, Olipop empowers consumers to make smarter, more enjoyable beverage choices.

name: KaseMe
description: A lifestyle brand specializing in high-quality, customizable phone cases and tech accessories that blend style, durability, and sustainability. Known for its bold, artistic designs, Kaseme offers a wide range of protective and stylish cases for various devices, allowing customers to express their individuality while protecting their technology. Each product is crafted with precision to ensure functionality and a premium feel. At the heart of Kaseme’s philosophy is a commitment to sustainability and local craftsmanship. The company utilizes eco-conscious materials and manufacturing practices, ensuring its products have a minimal environmental impact. By combining creativity, quality, and environmental responsibility, Kaseme has become a go-to choice for stylish, sustainable tech protection.

name: Nantucket Spider
description: A premium natural insect repellent brand committed to providing effective, eco-friendly solutions for outdoor enthusiasts. Known for its DEET-free formulas, the company offers a range of natural bug sprays and repellents crafted with essential oils to protect against mosquitoes, ticks, and other pests. Nantucket Spider’s mission is to make outdoor adventures safer and more enjoyable while minimizing environmental impact. Dedicated to sustainability, Nantucket Spider uses responsibly sourced ingredients and recyclable packaging in all its products. The brand’s emphasis on transparency, safety, and quality has made it a trusted choice for families, campers, and anyone seeking a natural alternative to conventional insect repellents.

name: ecoright
description: A sustainable lifestyle brand dedicated to crafting eco-friendly bags and accessories that blend style, functionality, and environmental responsibility. With a mission to combat single-use plastic pollution, EcoRight offers reusable alternatives like tote bags, backpacks, pouches, and lunch bags made from eco-conscious materials such as organic cotton and recycled fabric. Each product is designed to make sustainable living effortless and accessible. EcoRight is committed to reducing its environmental footprint through ethical manufacturing, recyclable packaging, and partnerships with global initiatives aimed at preserving the planet. The brand’s creative designs and commitment to sustainability have made it a favorite among eco-conscious consumers seeking products that are as kind to the environment as they are practical and stylish.

name: LouLou Lollipop
description: A modern lifestyle brand specializing in premium baby products that combine functionality, safety, and style. Renowned for its innovative teething accessories, swaddles, and silicone tableware, Loulou Lollipop crafts products designed to simplify parenting while adding a touch of elegance. The brand’s playful designs, inspired by creativity and love for little ones, make their products a favorite among modern families. Sustainability and quality are central to Loulou Lollipop’s ethos. The company prioritizes using non-toxic, eco-friendly materials and adheres to rigorous safety standards. By focusing on ethically made, beautifully designed, and sustainable products, Loulou Lollipop supports parents in creating a safe, stylish, and nurturing environment for their children.

name: Guests on Earth
description: A sustainable lifestyle brand dedicated to creating eco-friendly, reusable products that support a greener and more mindful way of living. Specializing in household and personal care items, Guests on Earth offers stylish, durable, and functional alternatives to single-use products, such as reusable bags, wraps, and cleaning essentials. The brand’s mission is to inspire individuals to embrace sustainability in their daily routines and treat the planet with care. Grounded in its commitment to environmental stewardship, Guests on Earth prioritizes the use of renewable resources, ethical manufacturing, and minimal-waste packaging. By blending thoughtful design with sustainability, the brand empowers consumers to make choices that benefit the environment while enhancing their everyday lives.

name: Brompton
description: An iconic British brand specializing in designing and manufacturing high-quality folding bicycles that blend functionality, durability, and style. Founded in London in 1975, Brompton has revolutionized urban commuting with its compact and portable bikes, designed to adapt seamlessly to modern city living. Each Brompton bike is crafted with precision, offering riders a smooth, efficient, and customizable experience for navigating urban environments. Sustainability and innovation are at the heart of Brompton’s ethos. The brand is committed to reducing its environmental impact by promoting cycling as an eco-friendly mode of transportation. By offering sustainable mobility solutions, Brompton empowers individuals to embrace greener commuting habits while enjoying the freedom and convenience of cycling.

name: The Coconut Cult
description: A health-focused food brand specializing in probiotic-rich coconut yogurt crafted to promote gut health and overall wellness. Made with organic coconut cream and powerful probiotic strains, The Coconut Cult’s products are designed to provide a delicious and nutrient-packed alternative to traditional yogurts. Known for its bold flavors and clean ingredients, the brand is beloved by health enthusiasts seeking functional foods that nourish the body. Rooted in sustainability and transparency, The Coconut Cult prioritizes organic, ethically sourced ingredients and eco-friendly packaging. The company’s commitment to creating high-quality, gut-friendly products reflects its mission to make healthy eating fun, accessible, and environmentally responsible.

name: Organico Realfoods
description: A leading organic food brand dedicated to providing high-quality, ethically sourced, and sustainable products. Specializing in pantry staples, snacks, and condiments, the brand offers a wide range of organic and eco-friendly options that prioritize health, taste, and environmental responsibility. Organico Realfoods combines traditional culinary values with modern sustainability practices, ensuring every product is as good for the planet as it is for the consumer. With a focus on transparency and sustainability, Organico Realfoods partners with ethical farmers and producers to deliver organic, non-GMO products free from artificial additives. The brand’s commitment to sustainable agriculture and eco-conscious operations has made it a trusted name for individuals and families seeking wholesome, environmentally friendly food options.

name: Trash Panda
description: A sustainability-driven brand dedicated to revolutionizing the sport of disc golf with eco-friendly products. Known for its discs made entirely from recycled materials, Trash Panda combines innovative design with a strong commitment to reducing plastic waste. The brand’s mission is to make disc golf accessible, fun, and environmentally responsible by offering high-quality gear that aligns with its zero-waste philosophy. Beyond its products, Trash Panda actively engages with the disc golf community and environmental advocates to promote sustainable practices both on and off the course. By blending passion for the sport with eco-consciousness, Trash Panda empowers players to enjoy the game while protecting the planet.

name: Laughing Gull Chocolates
description: A socially conscious craft chocolate company committed to creating delicious, high-quality confections while promoting sustainability and ethical practices. Specializing in handcrafted chocolates made from responsibly sourced cacao, Laughing Gull blends innovative flavors with traditional techniques to produce treats that delight the palate. The company’s mission is to craft chocolate that not only tastes exceptional but also supports a fair and environmentally friendly supply chain. Rooted in its dedication to sustainability, Laughing Gull Chocolates partners with farmers who prioritize eco-conscious and fair trade practices. The brand also emphasizes local ingredients and minimal packaging to reduce its environmental footprint. Through its chocolates, Laughing Gull inspires joy while contributing to a more equitable and sustainable world.

name: Inspiro Tequila
description: A premium tequila brand crafted by women, for women, with a focus on producing exceptional spirits that inspire confidence and connection. Handcrafted in Jalisco, Mexico, Inspiro Tequila uses 100% Blue Weber agave and traditional techniques to create smooth, additive-free tequilas that cater to the modern palate. The brand offers a refined and sophisticated tequila experience, ideal for sipping neat or enjoying in cocktails. At its core, Inspiro Tequila is dedicated to sustainability, authenticity, and empowerment. The brand is committed to environmentally conscious practices, from agave cultivation to eco-friendly packaging. By blending tradition with innovation, Inspiro Tequila celebrates the craftsmanship of tequila-making while encouraging women to explore and enjoy the tequila category.

name: Kimai
description: A luxury jewelry brand redefining fine jewelry with a commitment to sustainability, transparency, and modern craftsmanship. Specializing in lab-grown diamonds and recycled gold, Kimai offers exquisite, timeless pieces that align with eco-conscious values. By combining innovative materials with traditional techniques, Kimai delivers jewelry that is as ethical as it is beautiful, appealing to consumers seeking sustainable luxury. At the heart of Kimai’s philosophy is a dedication to reducing the environmental and social impact of traditional jewelry production. The brand prioritizes responsible sourcing and transparent practices, ensuring every piece is crafted with care and integrity. By marrying ethics with elegance, Kimai empowers customers to make thoughtful, meaningful choices in their jewelry purchases.

name: Groupe L’Occitane
description: A global, multi-brand company dedicated to creating and distributing high-quality, sustainably crafted beauty and wellness products. With a portfolio that includes L’Occitane en Provence, Melvita, and other renowned brands, the company emphasizes using natural and organic ingredients sourced responsibly from around the world. Known for its commitment to authenticity and environmental stewardship, Groupe L’Occitane blends traditional craftsmanship with modern innovation to provide luxurious products that respect people and the planet. Sustainability and social responsibility are at the heart of Groupe L’Occitane’s operations. The company focuses on reducing its ecological footprint through eco-friendly packaging, renewable energy use, and conservation initiatives. By fostering a culture of inclusivity and sustainability, Groupe L’Occitane continues to lead in the beauty industry with a strong commitment to ethical practices and environmental preservation.

name: LOOM Imports
description: An ethical home goods brand specializing in handcrafted textiles and décor that celebrate global artistry and craftsmanship. Partnering with skilled artisans from around the world, Loom Imports curates a collection of rugs, throws, pillows, and other home accents made with traditional techniques passed down through generations. Each piece tells a unique story, blending cultural heritage with modern design to create timeless and meaningful products. At the heart of Loom Imports is a commitment to sustainability, fair trade, and social impact. By working directly with artisans and using eco-friendly materials, the brand ensures its products are not only beautiful but also responsibly made. Loom Imports empowers artisans and supports sustainable practices, fostering a connection between consumers and the stories behind their homes.

name: Manitobah
description: An Indigenous-owned Canadian brand renowned for crafting authentic, high-quality footwear that celebrates the rich traditions of Indigenous artisans. Specializing in moccasins, boots, and slippers, Manitobah combines time-honored techniques with modern design to create footwear that is both stylish and functional. Each product is crafted with exceptional attention to detail, reflecting the cultural heritage and artistry of Indigenous communities. Rooted in its commitment to community and sustainability, Manitobah works with Indigenous artists and makers to preserve traditional craftsmanship while supporting economic empowerment. The brand also prioritizes the use of natural and sustainable materials to minimize its environmental footprint. Manitobah’s mission is to share the beauty and culture of Indigenous traditions through products that honor their history and respect the planet.

name: SENDY
description: An online marketplace and gear hub, enabling users across North America to buy, sell, and rent adventure sports equipment. Founded in late 2022 by professional snowboarder Travis Rice and freerider Cam Zink, Sendy aims to make outdoor sports more accessible and sustainable by promoting the reuse and sharing of high-quality gear.

name: Goods that Matter
description: A New Orleans-based eco-conscious brand dedicated to creating everyday design goods with extraordinary impact. Founded in 2010 by Tippy Tippens, the company offers a range of handmade products, including candles, bags, tees, accessories, notebooks, cards, blankets, and soaps, all crafted from eco-friendly materials in the United States. Each product is designed for everyday use and contributes to unique social and environmental causes, with 10% of all proceeds donated to initiatives that enhance community health, happiness, and sustainability.

name: Sanpellegrino
description: An iconic Italian beverage brand celebrated for its premium sparkling mineral water and a variety of flavored sparkling drinks. Established in 1899, the brand draws its water from natural springs in the Italian Alps, renowned for their exceptional purity and mineral balance. Sanpellegrino combines tradition and innovation to deliver refreshing beverages that pair effortlessly with fine dining and everyday moments alike. As a leader in sustainability, Sanpellegrino is committed to protecting natural resources, reducing its environmental footprint, and promoting recycling through its operations. The brand’s dedication to quality, heritage, and environmental stewardship has made it a global symbol of Italian excellence.

name: Coradorables
description: A family-run, woman-owned, and Black-owned fashion brand based in Honolulu, Hawaii, specializing in heirloom-quality resort wear and accessories for children and adults. Founded in 2010 by designer Cora Spearman, the brand combines a classic design aesthetic with elements of innovation and fun, reflecting the vibrant local culture and beauty of diversity. Each piece is meticulously crafted from hand-selected textiles and custom patterns, ensuring exclusivity and timeless style.

name: Sachai Tea Company
description: Founded in 2015 by Rebecca and Clint Denson, is a Birmingham, Alabama-based tea producer specializing in authentic masala chai concentrates and loose-leaf teas sourced directly from small-scale Indian tea farmers. The name "Sachai" is derived from the Hindi word "sach," meaning "truth," reflecting the company's commitment to transparency and authenticity in its products.

name: Sportiqe
description: An active lifestyle retail company that curates a diverse collection of over 500 brands from more than 30 countries, offering unique, functional, fashionable, and purposeful products for various aspects of life, including work, play, and home. Founded in 2009 and headquartered in San Francisco, California, Sportique's mission is to drive the discovery of thoughtfully designed items that cater to individuals who appreciate quality and reject the status quo.

name: Bon Ton Toys
description: Established in 1933 and based in Amsterdam, is a renowned plush toy manufacturer dedicated to creating high-quality, durable plush toys while championing environmental sustainability and ethical production practices. The company collaborates with iconic characters like Miffy and Snoopy, as well as partners with the World Wildlife Fund (WWF) to produce eco-friendly plush animals.

name: VAHDAM India
description: A digitally native, global wellness brand that brings the finest Indian teas, superfoods, and spices directly to consumers in over 130 countries. By eliminating intermediaries, VAHDAM ensures that its products are garden-fresh and of the highest quality. The company is committed to ethical sourcing and sustainability, with a portion of its revenue dedicated to supporting the education of its farmers' children.

name: Room & Board
description: An American furniture and home décor brand specializing in modern, timeless designs crafted with quality and sustainability in mind. Founded in 1980 and headquartered in Minneapolis, Minnesota, the company is renowned for its commitment to American craftsmanship, partnering with skilled artisans and manufacturers across the United States to create furniture built to last. Room & Board’s product range includes living room, bedroom, dining, office furniture, and customizable options to suit diverse lifestyles and spaces. Sustainability is at the core of Room & Board’s mission. The company uses responsibly sourced materials, minimizes waste, and invests in eco-conscious practices to reduce its environmental footprint. With its dedication to quality, ethical production, and sustainability, Room & Board has become a trusted choice for those seeking furniture that blends style with substance.

name: ID Geneve
description: A pioneering Swiss watchmaking company founded in 2020, dedicated to merging traditional craftsmanship with sustainable innovation. Based in Geneva, the company specializes in creating luxury timepieces crafted from 100% recycled stainless steel and other eco-friendly materials, embodying a commitment to circular economy principles. By focusing on environmental responsibility, ID Genève aims to redefine the luxury watch industry, offering products that resonate with individuals concerned about climate change and seeking to make a positive social and environmental impact.

name: Earth Breeze
description: An eco-friendly consumer goods company specializing in sustainable laundry detergent solutions. Founded in 2020 by Jon Wedel, the company offers innovative products such as Eco Sheets—concentrated, biodegradable laundry detergent sheets designed to reduce plastic waste and minimize environmental impact. Earth Breeze is committed to providing effective cleaning solutions while promoting environmental regeneration and social responsibility.

name: Coop's
description: Established in 2008 and based in Boston, Massachusetts, is a family-owned producer of all-natural dessert toppings, renowned for their award-winning hot fudge and caramel sauces. Handcrafted in small batches, Coop's products are made with meticulously sourced, high-quality ingredients, ensuring rich and indulgent flavors without the use of artificial additives or preservatives. Their offerings include Original Hot Fudge, Mocha Hot Fudge, Salted Caramel Sauce, and a vegan hot fudge option, catering to a diverse range of taste preferences.

name: Partake Brewing
description: Founded in 2017 by Ted Fleming, is a Canadian company specializing in non-alcoholic craft beers that offer the authentic taste of traditional brews without the alcohol content. Headquartered in Calgary, Alberta, Partake Brewing has become a leader in the non-alcoholic beer market across North America, providing a range of styles that cater to beer enthusiasts seeking a healthier or alcohol-free lifestyle.

name: Gibsons Games
description: Established in 1919 by Harry Percy Gibson, is a family-owned UK company renowned for producing high-quality board games and jigsaw puzzles. Headquartered in Sutton, England, the company is now managed by the fourth generation of the Gibson family, maintaining a legacy of bringing people together through engaging and entertaining products.

name: Sheet Society
description: An Australian bedding brand founded in 2017 by Hayley and Andy Worley, specializing in high-quality, stylish, and sustainable bed linens. Based in Melbourne, the company offers a diverse range of products, including fitted sheets, flat sheets, pillowcases, and quilt covers, crafted from premium materials such as long-staple cotton and French flax linen.
